<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,152,467]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,369,395]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Venugopal &amp; Thomas, 2019" authorityName="Venugopal &amp; Thomas" authorityYear="2019" box="[323,625,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pherosophus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devagiriensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[323,625,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">Pherosophus devagiriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[634,725,369,395]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[634,725,369,395]" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1798" box="[933,1035,369,395]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pheropsophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
<emphasis box="[933,1035,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="86">P. hilaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from it by head entirely yellow, pronotum with bright yellow spot not reaching the lateral margin, lateral margin black, pronontal median furrow deep, disc glabrous and shiny, elytral humeral spot very small, elytral yellow apical band narrow.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
